## `app/(tabs)/_layout.tsx`
```tsx
import React from 'react';
import { Tabs } from 'expo-router';
import FloatingTabBar from '@/components/FloatingTabBar';
import { useUser } from '@/contexts/UserContext';
import { colors } from '@/styles/commonStyles';

export default function TabLayout() {
  const { user } = useUser();
  const isClient = user?.userType === 'client';
  const isProvider = user?.userType === 'provider';
  const clientTabs = [
    { name: 'index', title: 'Home', icon: 'home' },
    { name: 'profile', title: 'Profile', icon: 'person' },
  ];
  const providerTabs = [
    { name: 'index', title: 'Gigs', icon: 'work' },
    { name: 'profile', title: 'Profile', icon: 'person' },
  ];
  const tabs = isClient ? clientTabs : providerTabs;
  return (
    <React.Fragment>
      <Tabs
        screenOptions={{ headerShown: false }}
        tabBar={(props) => <FloatingTabBar {...props} tabs={tabs} />}
      >
        <Tabs.Screen name="index" />
        <Tabs.Screen name="profile" />
      </Tabs>
    </React.Fragment>
  );
}
```

---

## `app/(tabs)/_layout.ios.tsx`
```tsx
import React from 'react';
import { useUser } from '@/contexts/UserContext';
import { NativeTabs, Icon, Label } from 'expo-router/unstable-native-tabs';
import { colors } from '@/styles/commonStyles';

export default function TabLayout() {
  const { user } = useUser();
  const isClient = user?.userType === 'client';
  return (
    <NativeTabs tintColor={colors.primary}>
      <NativeTabs.Trigger name="index">
        <Label>{isClient ? 'Home' : 'Gigs'}</Label>
        <Icon sf={{ default: isClient ? 'house' : 'briefcase', selected: isClient ? 'house.fill' : 'briefcase.fill' }} drawable={isClient ? 'home' : 'work'} />
      </NativeTabs.Trigger>
      <NativeTabs.Trigger name="profile">
        <Label>Profile</Label>
        <Icon sf={{ default: 'person', selected: 'person.fill' }} drawable="person" />
      </NativeTabs.Trigger>
    </NativeTabs>
  );
}
```

---

## `app/(tabs)/index.tsx` (Android/Web — 964 lines)
The tab `index` screen for Android/Web. For **clients** it renders the full "Post a Gig" form inline (category, date, time, address, description, duration, gender, payment). For **providers** it shows either a subscription prompt or a list of available gigs with "Accept Gig" buttons. Uses `apiCall` from `@/utils/api`. Has `MessageModal` for success/error feedback. Resets form on success. Does **not** navigate away after posting — stays on the home tab.

Key details:
- `handlePostGig` posts to `/api/gigs` with `clientId`, `category`, `serviceDate`, `serviceTime`, `address`, `description`, `durationDays`, `durationHours`, `paymentOffer`, optional `preferredGender`
- `handleAcceptGig` PUTs to `/api/gigs/${gigId}/accept` with `{ providerId }`
- `fetchAvailableGigs` GETs `/api/gigs/matches/${provider.id}`

---

## `app/(tabs)/index.ios.tsx` (iOS — 932 lines)
Identical logic to `index.tsx` but uses raw `fetch` with `Constants.expoConfig?.extra?.backendUrl` instead of `apiCall`. Wraps client view in `<React.Fragment>` with `<Stack.Screen options={{ title: 'Post a Gig', headerLargeTitle: true }} />`. No `isMountedRef` guard.

---

## `app/(tabs)/(home)/_layout.tsx`
```tsx
import { Platform } from 'react-native';
import { Stack } from 'expo-router';

export default function HomeLayout() {
  return (
    <Stack>
      <Stack.Screen
        name="index"
        options={{
          headerShown: Platform.OS === 'ios',
          title: 'Home'
        }}
      />
    </Stack>
  );
}
```

---

## `app/(tabs)/(home)/index.tsx` (Android/Web — 823 lines)
A **separate** home screen inside `(home)/` group. For **clients**: shows logo, greeting, a red "Post a New Gig" button (`router.push('/post-gig')`), and a list of their posted gigs fetched from `/api/gigs/client/${user.id}`. For **providers**: shows available gigs from `/api/gigs/matches/${provider.id}`, separates direct offers (`selectedProviderId === provider.id && status === 'pending_acceptance'`) from regular open gigs, with Accept/Decline buttons. Has polling every 5s when direct offers exist.

---

## `app/(tabs)/(home)/index.ios.tsx` (iOS — 354 lines)
Simplified iOS version of `(home)/index.tsx`. Client view: logo, greeting, "Post a New Gig" button → `router.push('/post-gig')`, posted gigs list (renders `gig.title` only — **note: no `gig.category`/`gig.description`/status badge**). Provider view: subscribe card or gigs list (also renders `gig.title` only). No direct offer handling, no modal.

---

## `app/(tabs)/profile.tsx` (Android/Web — 932 lines)
Client profile shows: logo, avatar initials (red circle), name, email. Then for clients: recent gig card (fetched from `/api/gigs/client/${user.id}`), matched providers list with Select buttons, countdown timer (180s), waiting state. For providers: subscription status card. Both: Account Information section (type, county, org, gender, phone). Red "Log Out" button → `logout()` + `router.replace('/role-select')`. Polls every 5s when gig is open. Uses `useFocusEffect` to refetch on tab focus.

---

## `app/(tabs)/profile.ios.tsx` (iOS — 932 lines)
**Identical logic and JSX to `profile.tsx`** — same component, same API calls, same layout. Only differences:
- `scrollContent` `paddingTop` is `16` (not `Platform.OS === 'android' ? 48 : 16`)
- `SafeAreaView` uses `theme.colors.background` instead of hardcoded `'#FFFFFF'`
- No `Platform` import

---

## `app/post-gig.tsx` (793 lines)
A standalone Stack screen (outside tabs). Same form as `index.tsx` client view. On success shows `SuccessModal`, then on close navigates `router.replace('/(tabs)/profile')` with a 300ms timeout. On error shows `ErrorModal`. Has `mountedRef` and `navigationTimeoutRef` cleanup. `Stack.Screen` sets `title: 'Post a Gig'` but `_layout.tsx` overrides it with `headerShown: false` for the `post-gig` route.

---

## `app/_layout.tsx` (163 lines)
```tsx
// Root layout wraps: GestureHandlerRootView > ThemeProvider > UserProvider > WidgetProvider
// Stack screens:
//   index          — headerShown: false
//   role-select    — headerShown: false
//   register-client — headerShown: false
//   register-provider — headerShown: false
//   subscription-payment — headerShown: false
//   post-gig       — headerShown: false   ← NOTE: overrides post-gig's own Stack.Screen header
//   payment-simulator — headerShown: false
//   (tabs)         — headerShown: false
// Also renders NetworkErrorModal when isConnected === false
// No SafeAreaProvider wrapper
```

---

## Key observations for your review:

1. **`post-gig` header is hidden** — `_layout.tsx` sets `headerShown: false` for `post-gig`, so the `Stack.Screen title: 'Post a Gig'` inside `post-gig.tsx` has no effect. There is no back button visible.

2. **Two parallel "Post a Gig" implementations** — `(tabs)/index.tsx` has the full form inline (stays on tab after posting), while `(home)/index.tsx` navigates to `/post-gig` (separate screen). The `(tabs)/index` route and `(home)/index` route coexist — which one renders depends on which tab group is active.

3. **`(home)/index.ios.tsx` renders `gig.title`** but the API likely returns `gig.category`/`gig.description` — this would show blank text for gig cards on iOS in the `(home)` group.

4. **`profile.ios.tsx` is a full copy of `profile.tsx`** — not a re-export, so no circular import risk.

5. **No `SafeAreaProvider`** in `_layout.tsx` — only `GestureHandlerRootView` at root.

